<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alternative_solution_arm  Entity: Alternative_solution  
   <express_ref linkend="alternative_solution:arm:Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution">
An <b>Alternative_solution</b> is the identification of one of potentially many mutually exclusive implementations of a <b>Product_function</b> or of a <b>Product_component</b>. 
An <b>Alternative_solution</b> may refer directly to the object to be implemented or to another Alternative_solution object. In the latter case it serves as a refinement of the referenced <b>Alternative_solution</b>. 
An <b>Alternative_solution</b> shall be instantiated only, if it is decomposed further into Product_component or Product_function objects. 
<note number="1"> An <b>Alternative_solution</b> may specify (through <b>Product_structure_relationship</b> with 'relation_type' 'functionality' or 'realization') a set of objects that jointly form this implementation.
</note><note number="2"> Each <b>Alternative_solution</b> may be any combination of <b>Final_solution</b>, <b>Supplier_solution</b>, and <b>Technical_solution</b>.
</note>An <b>Alternative_solution</b> is a type of <b>Complex_product</b>. 
Each <b>Alternative_solution</b> may be specialized as a <b>Technical_solution</b> or a <b>Supplier_solution</b>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
