<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution.id">
The <b>id</b> specifies the identifier of the <b>Alternative_solution</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alternative_solution_arm  Entity: Alternative_solution  Attribute: version_id 
   <express_ref linkend="alternative_solution:arm:Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution.version_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution.version_id">
The <b>version_id</b> identifies a version of the concept represented by an <b>Alternative_solution</b>. 
<note>  The <b>version_id</b> does not identify a version of its characterization in one or more application contexts.
</note>The <b>version_id</b> need not be specified for a particular <b>Alternative_solution</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alternative_solution_arm  Entity: Alternative_solution  Attribute: base_element 
   <express_ref linkend="alternative_solution:arm:Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution.base_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Alternative_solution.base_element">
The <b>base_element</b> specifies the object, for which the <b>Alternative_solution</b> provides a design alternative. All Alternative_solution objects for the same base_element are mutually exclusive.  
There shall be exactly one instance that defines the <b>base_element</b> for an <b>Alternative_solution</b>.
</ext_description>
