The actual_rate shall not be strictly negative.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alternative_solution_arm  Entity: Technical_solution  
   <express_ref linkend="alternative_solution:arm:Alternative_solution_arm.Technical_solution"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Technical_solution">
A <b>Technical_solution</b> is a type of <b>Alternative_solution</b> where the functional requirements are fulfilled in a particular technical way. 
<example>'gilded handle', 'unpolished handle' for <b>Product_component</b> 'handle' are examples for a <b>Technical_solution</b>.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Alternative_solution_arm  Entity: Technical_solution  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="alternative_solution:arm:Alternative_solution_arm.Technical_solution.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Alternative_solution_arm.Technical_solution.description">
The <b>description</b> specifies additional information about the <b>Technical_solution</b>. 
There shall be exactly one instance that defines the <b>description</b> for a <b>Technical_solution</b>.
</ext_description>
